oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Webb Pierce and Tommy Cash Singles
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Cash, Tommy; Guitar; Musical instruments; Offset printing; Pierce, Webb, 1921-1991;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: One color offset printing plate (red on silver) advertising Webb Pierce's song, "Fool, Fool, Fool," written by Max Powell and Wayne P. Walker, and Tommy Cash's song, "Tobacco Road," written by John D. Loudermilk. The plate features photographs of Webb Pierce and Tommy Cash.
